          "title": "[NBitcoin.Secp256k1] Operations involving Infinity  ",
          "body": "I think something is wrong with `NBitcoin.Secp256k1` code. The following test fails:\r\n\r\n```c#\r\n[Fact]\r\npublic void Comparison2()\r\n{\r\n\tvar inf = Scalar.One * GE.Infinity;\r\n\tAssert.True(inf.IsInfinity);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nOther similar test involving the point at infinity also fail. Probably this is because a lack of understanding from my side about the library:\r\n\r\n```c#\r\n[Fact]\r\npublic void Comparison2()\r\n{\r\n\tvar inf = GE.Infinity.ToGroupElementJacobian() + GE.Infinity;\r\n\tAssert.True(inf.IsInfinity);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nRelated #871 ",
